ecommerce platform like amazon,flipkart etc

functional requirements->
1. user should be able to search product based on name,category.
2. user should be able to see the product details, reviews and ratings.
3.user should select quantity of product and add to cart.
4. user should be able to checkout the product in cart and make payment.
5. user should be able to see the order details and status of order.
6.manage purchase of items which are in limited stock in high sale to avoid race condition

non-functional requirements->
scale of system- 50m daily active users
cap theorem -> currently required both (highly available in case of searching and seeing the products)
and need consistency in case of payment and inventory management.
latency- on search as well as on checkout.

core entities->
1.User
2.Product
3.Cart
4.Order
5.checkout

Api Designing->
1. GET-> v1/product/search/q={searchTerm}-> should return list of productIds: pagination
searchTerm can be name,category
2. GET-> v1/product/{productId}-> should return product details,price,availability
3. POST-> v1/user/{userId}/cart-> should add product to cart
Request body: { "productId": "123", "quantity": 2 }
4. GET-> v1/user/{userId}/cart-> should return cart details
5. POST-> v1/user/{userId}/checkout-> return orderId
Request body: { all products in cart with quantity}
v1/payment-> should make payment and confirm order
Request body: { "orderId": "123", "paymentMethod": "CREDIT_CARD", "details": { ... } }
6. GET-> v1/user/{userId}/orders-> should return list of orders
7. GET-> v1/order/{orderId}-> should return order details and status


